
Changes in version 1.2.0 - Logging Module Enhancements
    * Implemented comprehensive activity logging system
        - Added Logger class with centralized logging management
        - Session tracking with unique session IDs for each framework launch
        - Exploit execution logging with success/failure tracking
    * Added session management features
        - Auto-generated 8-character session IDs on framework startup
        - Session initialization logging with timestamps and dividers
        - Database integration for session state management
    * Enhanced exploit execution logging
        - Logs exploit type, target, and success status
        - Verbose mode support for argument tracking
        - Conditional argument logging based on VERBOSE_LOGGING database flag
        - Supports multiple argument formats (lists and strings)
    * Implemented log file management
        - Automatic directory creation for log storage
        - Persistent activity log at .data/.logs/activity.log
        - Silent error handling to prevent framework interruption
        - Log rotation feature to manage file sizes (5MB max per file)
        - Automatic archival of rotated logs with timestamp suffixes
    * Integration improvements
        - Seamless integration with exploit handler for automatic execution logging
        - Database-driven configuration for verbose logging levels
        - Backward-compatible error handling with existing error reporting

Changes in version 1.2.1 - Project-wide Improvements and Fixes
    * MacOS Compatibility Enhancements
        - Added dedicated MacOS setup scripts and requirements
        - Created MacOS-Setup directory with executable.sh, setup.py, and start.c
        - Updated aliases and configuration for MacOS environment
        - Added MacOS-specific requirements.txt
    * Exploit Handler Improvements
        - Enhanced exploit execution with better error handling
        - Added verbose argument logging to all exploit types (Python modules, scripts, C executables)
        - Improved logging integration for exploit success/failure tracking
        - Fixed various bugs in exploit handler logic
    * Database Module Updates
        - Added VERBOSE_LOGGING configuration support
        - Enhanced key mapping for database operations
        - Improved configuration management
    * Code Quality and Bug Fixes
        - Fixed typos in main.py, set.py, inputHandler.py, and other core files
        - Corrected syntax and logic errors in exploit handler
        - Updated error logging and history management
    * External Tools and Dependencies
        - Added proper citations for authors of external tools
        - Updated checksums for external tool verification
        - Enhanced encryption/decryption capabilities
        - Improved external tool integration
    * Documentation and UI Updates
        - Multiple README.md updates for better documentation
        - Updated help sections and banners
        - Enhanced logo and branding elements
    * Security and Stability Improvements
        - Strengthened error handling across modules
        - Improved session and history management
        - Enhanced data persistence and recovery
    * Development Environment Updates
        - Added PyCharm project configuration
        - Updated setup scripts for better cross-platform support
        - Improved build and compilation processes


